Sentencas: Planar solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operates at high temperature and requires a good creep strength to ensure the structure integrity.
Titulo: Simulation of creep and damage in the bonded compliant seal of planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This paper presents a creep and damage analysis of a bonded compliant seal (BCS) structure of a planar SOFC considering the effect of as-bonded residual stress and thermal stress, as well as the effect of filler metal and foil thickness.
Titulo: Simulation of creep and damage in the bonded compliant seal of planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A modified continuum creep-damage model is used in the finite, element simulation.
Titulo: Simulation of creep and damage in the bonded compliant seal of planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: It demonstrates that the BCS structure meets the requirement of the long-term operation at the high temperature of 600 C with an appropriate braze bonding process.
Titulo: Simulation of creep and damage in the bonded compliant seal of planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The results show that the failure location is not in the region of maximum creep deformation due to the effect of high level multi-axial stress which drastically decreases the multi-axial ductility.
Titulo: Simulation of creep and damage in the bonded compliant seal of planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Reasonably reducing the thickness of filler metal and foil can decrease the damage of the BCS structure.
Titulo: Simulation of creep and damage in the bonded compliant seal of planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Based on the consideration of creep and damage, it is proposed that the thickness of filler metal and foil should not exceed 0.1 and 0.05 mm, respectively.
Titulo: Simulation of creep and damage in the bonded compliant seal of planar solid oxide fuel cell
